DataElementConcept.preferredDefinition: the response to an assessment or evaluation of fatigue, characterized by a lessened capacity for work and reduced efficiency of accomplishment, usually accompanied by a feeling of weariness, sleepiness, or irritability.

ObjectClass.preferredDefinition: The state of weariness following a period of exertion, mental or physical, characterized by a decreased capacity for work and reduced efficiency to respond to stimuli.:Examination of the body by auscultation, palpation, percussion, inspection, and olfaction.
